<subSubSection id="C337088DF77FB13EB182FE4831BB418F" pageId="10" pageNumber="531" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F77FB13EB182FE48336341E8" blockId="10.[151,1437,295,753]" pageId="10" pageNumber="531">
<collectionCode id="ED3CC3C3F77FB13EB182FE4832C2428C" box="[199,251,439,465]" pageId="10" pageNumber="531">TYPE</collectionCode>
MATERIAL: Sundevall stated in his original description (1850: 109) that he had data for both male and female, and according to his acquisition catalogue, 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF77FB13EB3A2FE2431AD42B7" box="[743,916,475,501]" pageId="10" pageNumber="531" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
were available to him in 1850. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F77FB13EB442FE243329415B" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." pageId="10" pageNumber="531" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 79)</bibRefCitation>
referred to NRM 569752 [7413] as a “type”, which we treat as a 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F77FB13EB550FE003645415B" box="[1045,1148,511,537]" pageId="10" pageNumber="531">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation of this adult female collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F77FB13EB01DFDDC33D6417F" box="[344,495,547,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="531" value="1840-06-30">
30 June 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F77FB13EB0F2FDDC33D6417F" box="[439,495,547,573]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6736" pageId="10" pageNumber="531" unit="in" value="1840.0">1840</quantity>
</date>
in Durban. The 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF77FB13EB3EFFDDC31B5417F" box="[682,908,547,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="531" type="generic" typeStatus="paralectotypes">three paralectotypes</specimenCount>
are: NRM 569753 [7411], a male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F77FB13EB4C5FDDC33334123" pageId="10" pageNumber="531" value="1841-05-30">
30 May 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F77FB13EB197FDB833334123" box="[210,266,583,609]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.67614" pageId="10" pageNumber="531" unit="in" value="1841.0">1841</quantity>
</date>
in Durban; NRM 534136 [7412], a mount of a male, collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F77FB13EB29DFDB8368A4123" box="[984,1203,583,609]" pageId="10" pageNumber="531" value="1840-09-14">
14 September 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F77FB13EB53EFDB8368A4123" box="[1147,1203,583,609]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6736" pageId="10" pageNumber="531" unit="in" value="1840.0">1840</quantity>
</date>
in Durban; a female [4831], collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F77FB13EB01EFD9433D341C7" box="[347,490,619,645]" pageId="10" pageNumber="531" value="1839-07-20">
20 July 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F77FB13EB0F7FD9433D341C7" box="[434,490,619,645]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.67106" pageId="10" pageNumber="531" unit="in" value="1839.0">1839</quantity>
</date>
in Durban, sent on exchange to 
<collectingRegion id="49E995E4F77FB13EB214FD9431AE41C7" box="[849,919,619,645]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="10" pageNumber="531">Berlin</collectingRegion>
in 1853 (but probably no longer present in the ZMB collection).
</paragraph>
